SPACEX.name: SpaceX
SPACEX.tagline: Designing, manufacturing and launching advanced rockets and spacecraft to revolutionize space technology and enable humanity to become a multi-planetary species
SPACEX.overview: Space Exploration Technologies Corp. (SpaceX) is an American aerospace manufacturer and space transportation company founded in 2002 by Elon Musk. The company designs, manufactures, and launches advanced rockets and spacecraft with the goal of reducing space transportation costs and enabling Mars colonization. SpaceX operates the Falcon 9 and Falcon Heavy rockets, the Dragon spacecraft, and is developing the Starship—the largest and most powerful rocket ever built. The company's Starlink satellite internet constellation has become its largest revenue driver, with 2025 revenue projected at $13.3 billion. SpaceX is in talks to raise new funding at a $400 billion valuation as of July 2025, making it one of the most valuable private companies in the world. Total funding raised to date: $11.9 billion over 31 rounds from 229 investors.

STRIPE.name: Stripe
STRIPE.tagline: Building economic infrastructure that enables businesses of all sizes to accept payments and grow online
STRIPE.overview: Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform founded in 2010 by Irish brothers Patrick and John Collison. The company provides payment processing, billing, and financial APIs for businesses of all sizes. Stripe achieved profitability in 2024 and reached $107B valuation by September 2025—surpassing its 2021 peak of $95B. The platform processes $1.4T in annual payment volume (~1.3% of global GDP) for half the Fortune 100 and 78% of Forbes AI 50 companies including OpenAI, Anthropic, and NVIDIA. In 2025, Stripe acquired Bridge (stablecoin platform) for $1.1B and launched the world's first AI foundation model for payments.

SHEIN.name: Shein
SHEIN.tagline: Global fast-fashion platform leveraging AI-driven supply chain and real-time trend detection to deliver affordable fashion worldwide
SHEIN.overview: Shein is a Singapore-headquartered fast-fashion company founded in 2008 by Chris Xu (Sky Xu) in China. The company has become the world's largest fast-fashion retailer with 18% global market share, generating $38 billion in revenue in 2024 (up 23% YoY). Shein's AI-driven supply chain enables it to go from design to production in 3-7 days, adding thousands of new styles daily. The company has struggled with IPO plans—after failing to gain SEC approval for a US listing, Shein filed with the London Stock Exchange in June 2024, gaining FCA approval in April 2025. In mid-2025, Shein also filed for a Hong Kong IPO. Net profit fell 40% in 2024 to ~$1 billion due to increased competition from Temu and rising tariffs affecting the de minimis exemption.

SNYK.name: Snyk
SNYK.tagline: Securing cloud-native applications by finding and fixing vulnerabilities in code, dependencies, and infrastructure
SNYK.overview: Snyk is a developer-first security platform founded in 2015 that helps developers find and fix vulnerabilities in code, dependencies, containers, and infrastructure as code. The company pioneered the shift-left security movement. Snyk reached $300M ARR in October 2024 with 5,000+ enterprise customers and is targeting cash-flow positive in 2025. The company's AI-native SAST product (Snyk Code) alone generates $100M ARR. While Snyk reached an $8.5B valuation in 2021, recent valuations have compressed. In November 2024, Snyk acquired Probely for dynamic application security testing.

SAFE-SUPERINTELLIGENCE.name: Safe Superintelligence
SAFE-SUPERINTELLIGENCE.tagline: Stealth AI lab focused solely on developing safe superintelligent systems, founded by former OpenAI co-founder Ilya Sutskever
SAFE-SUPERINTELLIGENCE.overview: Safe Superintelligence Inc. (SSI) is an AI research company co-founded by Ilya Sutskever, Daniel Gross, and Daniel Levy in June 2024 with a singular mission: building safe superintelligence. Sutskever, a legendary figure in AI who co-founded OpenAI and led the development of GPT models, became CEO in July 2025 after Gross departed for Meta. SSI reached a staggering $32 billion valuation in April 2025 after raising $2 billion led by Greenoaks Capital—a 6.4x valuation increase from its $5B September 2024 round. The company has raised $3 billion total from Alphabet, NVIDIA, Andreessen Horowitz, Sequoia, DST Global, and Lightspeed. Operating with only ~20 employees, SSI has no products, no revenue, and no commercial ambitions—it exists solely to solve the superintelligence alignment problem. In April 2025, Google Cloud announced a partnership to provide TPUs for SSI's research.

products.description: Developing provably safe methods for building superintelligent AI systems that remain aligned with human values

SCALE-AI.name: Scale AI
SCALE-AI.tagline: The data infrastructure platform accelerating AI development for enterprises and government
SCALE-AI.overview: Scale AI is the leading data infrastructure company powering the development of artificial intelligence. Founded in 2016, Scale provides high-quality training data and AI infrastructure to enterprises, AI labs, and government agencies. With 90% of business now driven by generative AI, Scale has become essential infrastructure for companies training large language models and other AI systems. In June 2025, Meta acquired a 49% stake in Scale for $14.3 billion, valuing the company at over $29 billion. The deal brought founder Alexandr Wang to Meta to lead a new "superintelligence" research lab.

SUPABASE.name: Supabase
SUPABASE.tagline: Open-source Firebase alternative providing PostgreSQL backend-as-a-service platform
SUPABASE.overview: Supabase is an open-source Backend-as-a-Service platform founded in 2020 by Paul Copplestone and Ant Wilson. Built on PostgreSQL, Supabase provides developers with a complete backend infrastructure including database, authentication, real-time subscriptions, storage, and serverless functions. The company has positioned itself as "the open-source Firebase alternative" and has become the go-to database for the vibe coding movement, powering AI-assisted development tools like Cursor, Bolt, Lovable, and Figma. As of October 2025, Supabase has achieved a $5 billion valuation following its Series E funding round, serving over 4 million developers who manage more than 3.5 million databases globally.

highlights.text: Raised $100M Series E at $5B valuation, led by Accel and Peak XV (Oct 2025).
Raised $200M Series D at $2B valuation, led by Accel (Apr 2025).
Achieved $70M ARR, up from $20M at end of 2024.
Acquired OrioleDB to enhance PostgreSQL performance (Apr 2024).
Grew from 1M to 4M+ developers in under a year.

investors.name: PostgreSQL Database: Full-featured relational database with instant setup.

SYNTHESIA.name: Synthesia
SYNTHESIA.tagline: The world's leading AI video communications platform for enterprises, creating professional videos using AI avatars and text
SYNTHESIA.overview: Synthesia is a British multinational AI company based in London that develops software for creating AI-generated video content. Founded in 2017 by Victor Riparbelli, Steffen Tjerrild, Professor Matthias Niessner, and Professor Lourdes Agapito from UCL, Stanford, TUM, and Cambridge, Synthesia's mission is to empower everyone to make video content without cameras, microphones, or studios. The company's software algorithm mimics speech and facial movements based on video recordings to create text-to-speech videos that look and sound like real individuals. As of January 2025, Synthesia has achieved a valuation of $2.1 billion and serves over 65,000 businesses, including more than 70% of the Fortune 100 companies. With over $100 million in annual recurring revenue and 500+ employees globally, Synthesia leads the enterprise AI video communications market.
